snippet.title: DOS Games Vol. 2 - Larax & Zaco
snippet.description:
Vol. 1 was Bat'n'Ball.
Here's Larax & Zaco, an old game, which it's last version got to be shared recently. It works with DOSBox with no problem.
I include a Download Link of it, as a Pack, that contains:
Version 1.0, 1.5S (Unfindable on Internet) and 1.8b which is the last version, played in the video.

Link :
https://mega.nz/#!kFRngTJA!ZeA-P2CPgp4hutAtB-vl6jgG4iNiGW90Vzd7aQ8CnKM

My thoughts :
This is a game i played and discovered long ago (2001, i think.) on a DOS Games CD Pack that included that rare to find version 1.5S.
If there's something i understood, the game is about to find some specific item, and get all of them, and then, use your bombs, to destroy everything, which is quite fun. I really suggest to play it.
